OL,3,CTfL to ban non-folding e-bikes
OL,5,F"To ensure the safety of the network
OL,6,Ffor customers and staff, customers in
OL,7,Fpossession of non-foldable e-bikes
OL,8,Fwill not be permitted to travel on
OL,9,Fmost TfL services, including on the
OL,10,FTube, Overground, Elizabeth line and
OL,11,FDLR.
OL,13,F"The ban includes all non-folding e-
OL,14,Fbikes, including standard cycles that
OL,15,Fhave been converted to e-bikes using
OL,16,Fconversion kits."
OL,18,FFinn Brennan, Aslef's organiser on
OL,19,FLondon Underground, said: "This is
OL,20,Fsomething that Aslef's health and
OL,21,Fsafety reps have long campaigned for.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/8
