OL,3,CTfL to ban non-folding e-bikes
OL,5,FThe Deputy commissioner for
OL,6,Fprevention, protection and policy,
OL,7,FCharlie Pugsley, said: "We welcome
OL,8,Fthis move by Transport for London
OL,9,Ffollowing their detailed safety
OL,10,Freview, as it acknowledges the risks
OL,11,Fthat we know e-bike batteries can pose.
OL,13,F"While we recognise the sustainable
OL,14,Fbenefits e-bikes, and micromobility
OL,15,Fgenerally, bring to our city, the
OL,16,Freality is that across London we have
OL,17,Fbeen seeing an e-bike or e-scooter
OL,18,Ffire every other day, on average, and
OL,19,Fwe have particular concern about the
OL,20,Frisk posed by conversion kits or
OL,21,Fmodified e-bikes.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/8
