OL,3,CTfL to ban non-folding e-bikes
OL,5,F"The risk doesn't disappear just
OL,6,Fbecause a bike folds in half. To truly
OL,7,Fprotect people on the network, TfL
OL,8,Fmust extend the ban to include all e-
OL,9,Fbikes.
OL,11,F"Our members see first-hand the
OL,12,Fdangers these bikes pose. Any e-bike
OL,13,Fwith a faulty battery, poor wiring or
OL,14,Fa cheap charger is a fire risk,
OL,15,Fregardless of whether it folds or not."
